        "description": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to the clinical failure modes of interest (construct stiffness relates to load sharing, yield force to permanent deformation onset, force at 40 mm to post-yield structural integrity). Gradation 3 achieved: direct mechanistic linkage between QoIs and clinical endpoints documented."
